    "The human victims of [harmful algorithms], we'll see time and again, are held to a far higher standard of evidence than the algorithms themselves.\"",
    "(O'Neil 2016, p.11) Increasingly, regulators are stepping in to require service providers to ensure equitable treatment.",
    "This tends to naturally create a top-down approach, where it is the responsibility of service providers to try to put in place measures to improve the fairness and safety of their systems.",
    "A limitation, however, comes from the fact that this setup does not afford meaningful avenues for the uptake of relevant epistemic resources that have already been identified by the affected individuals and communities.",
    "An example where one can observe such a trend is the way social media feeds and personalised digital environments structure our individual experience of the digital world."
